,Recommended,502940,29693313,Posted: 4 February,all,A very hot piece of Kek™,"A without a doubt interesting little game.Calm down, Stalin takes place during the cold war, and you play as. Who else? Stalin, who fends off an enemy invasion simply by menancingly holding his finger above the large red button which will launch an attack on the rest of the world. The game progressively gets harder, as you are given more and more chores to tend to, such as answering your phone, hitting your poorly working office lamp and later on assassinating people.At first i thought this game was just a simple time waster, and to some degree it is, however there's more too it than meets the eye.For example:-You need to maintain the integrity of your country, which slowly but surely worsen with each 'story' mission you do, abruptly ending calls, or not answering them at all will decrease the country integrity after you've unlocked the phone-You get stressed by things around you, smoking your pipe is a way of relieving stress but you can't do both that and hold your hand near the button so you will need to spend every second you get very wisely to avoid getting invaded, having your country colapse or accidentally launching an attack.You shouldn't expect to get thousands of hours worth of gameplay out of this, but it is a entertaining game to boot up now and then, and it's nice seeing a game with a silly premise get released these days but actually have a bit more to it than ""Lel gaiz, looks it's so random xDDD"""
