76561198356092365,Recommended,502940,30493288,Posted: 13 March,all,TheNightmareTrooper,"This is probably one of the most bizarre games I have played in quite awhile, but it is incredibly fun. You take control of the arms of Joseph Stalin to complete the tasks of the nation by answering phone calls, stamping documents, and threatening enemies of the state by means of nuclear warfare with your finger on the button (not figuratively in the least). A plethora of distractions stand in your way in the form of a flickering lamp, political dissidents that need to be shot, and good ol' fashion stress (remedied with vodka and pipe smoke). The controls and coordination take some getting used to, but after you figure it out, it is not really that bad at all. There are enough stages and achievements (which personally, I found the names of the achievements to be particularly funny) to keep you occupied for hours. All in all, the game is worthwhile if you just want to kill some time in a silly manner or just to live out your fantasy of being a dictator in charge of a nation."
