76561198045070838,Recommended,502940,29412844,Posted: 21 January,all,Rubber2Duck,"This game is really fun!! if you like the stress of multi-tasking to the extremeI have really only played 2 to 2 and a half hours of this game (had this game running in the background while i watched a movie) but it was really enjoyable, but frustrating at times, which I will get into later. The game helps ease you into each of the mechanics, giving you a level where you only have to deal with the new mechanic and nothing else (other than the button). Each of the mechanics have a little""things""  to it, like a phone that rings, if you fail to pick up or hang up, you lose integrity, or punching bag that helps keep away stress, it was always an enjoyable when I find out I get a new toy to play with, and then tear my eyes out when its fully encorporated.Then there are the frustrating parts.The button is placed right next to the phone and if you accidently move to get the phone too low, you press the button and its game over for you, which happend to me about 3 seconds away from victory :(. It also gets a bit too hectic, you have to multi task... as far as I recall 9 different items, which, if you are bad at paying attention, will screw you over  in the endAnd thats my very speedly made review, in the end, its a quick game for an okay price, I would like to see it dropped a bit, it will make you rage, it will make you weap tears of joy when you beat the insanely long final level, and, there are quite a few youtubers you could watch to get a feel for the game and see if its your cup of tea, thats how i found it, anyways thanks for sitting through this, have a good day :D"
